Amanda Knox was exonerated of the 2007 murder of British student Meredith Kercher in March . 
  Her biographer Douglas Preston says she is suffering from PTSD and has spent millions on legal fees . 
  Knox and her ex-boyfriend Raffaele Sollecito spent four years in prison for the murder of Kercher . 
  The 27-year-old spent eight years fighting her conviction in Italy . 
  She was released in March after the Italian Supreme Court overturned her conviction . 
  Preston says Knox was threatened with rape in prison . 
  He says she has been left penniless and traumatized by the ordeal . 
 